# Swarm Architecture

## Core constraints

- **One experiment running at a time** — `POST /start` returns 409 if another is running
- **Agent produces new code between trials** — refill invokes agent runner (cursor-agent or shell), never creates dummy/duplicate trials
- **Workers run real `train.py`** — ~5-20 min per trial on MPS, not toy scripts
- **CLI and UI must be equivalent** — every UI action has a `curl` equivalent; test both

## Key files

- `swarm/orchestrator.py` — FastAPI server, all API endpoints + UI routes + background tasks
- `swarm/worker.py` — worker process (register, heartbeat, claim, train, complete)
- `swarm/agent.py` — agent runner interface (CursorAgentRunner, ShellAgentRunner, NoopAgentRunner)
- `swarm/schema.sql` — SQLite schema (workers, experiments, trials)
- `swarm/db.py` — database helper
- `swarm/templates/` — Jinja2 + HTMX templates
- `swarm/static/style.css` — dark theme CSS

## API response conventions

- Errors: `{"error": "<code>", "detail": "<message>"}` for all 4xx/5xx
- Trials list: `{"trials": [...], "page": 1, "per_page": 50, "total": N, "total_pages": M}` (paginated)
- Timestamps: ISO 8601 UTC
- Structlog events: use exact event names (e.g. `server.trial_completed`, `worker.claimed`)

